{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":574,"text":"Africa is booming."},{"time":2361,"text":"Per capita incomes since the year 2000"},{"time":4866,"text":"have doubled,"},{"time":6466,"text":"and this boom is impacting on everyone."},{"time":9841,"text":"Life expectancy has increased by one year"},{"time":12667,"text":"every three years for the last decade."},{"time":15417,"text":"That means if an African child is born today,"},{"time":18902,"text":"rather than three days ago,"},{"time":20690,"text":"they will get an extra day of life"},{"time":22577,"text":"at the end of their lifespan."},{"time":24600,"text":"It's that quick."},{"time":26391,"text":"And HIV infection rates are down 27 percent:"},{"time":30503,"text":"600,000 less people a year are getting HIV"},{"time":34753,"text":"in sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":37217,"text":"The battle against malaria is being won,"},{"time":40279,"text":"with deaths from malaria down 27 percent,"},{"time":43079,"text":"according to the latest World Bank data."},{"time":44841,"text":"And malaria nets actually are playing a role in that."},{"time":47938,"text":"This shouldn't surprise us,"},{"time":50110,"text":"because actually, everybody grows."},{"time":52859,"text":"If you go back to Imperial Rome"},{"time":54835,"text":"in the Year 1 A.D.,"},{"time":57040,"text":"there was admittedly about 1,800 years"},{"time":59338,"text":"where there wasn't an awful lot of growth."},{"time":61585,"text":"But then the people that the Romans"},{"time":63577,"text":"would have called Scottish barbarians, my ancestors,"},{"time":67392,"text":"were actually part of the Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":69512,"text":"and in the 19th century, growth began to accelerate,"},{"time":72200,"text":"and you saw that get quicker and quicker,"},{"time":75240,"text":"and it's been impacting everyone."},{"time":78000,"text":"It doesn't matter if this is the jungles of Singapore"},{"time":80615,"text":"or the tundra of northern Finland."},{"time":82865,"text":"Everybody gets involved. It's just a matter of when"},{"time":85786,"text":"the inevitable happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88120,"text":"Among the reasons I think it's happening right now"},{"time":90741,"text":"is the quality of the leadership across Africa."},{"time":94223,"text":"I think most of us would agree that in the 1990s,"},{"time":97541,"text":"the greatest politician in the world was African,"},{"time":101237,"text":"but I'm meeting brilliant people"},{"time":103848,"text":"across the continent the entire time,"},{"time":105712,"text":"and they're doing the reforms"},{"time":107280,"text":"which have transformed the economic situation"},{"time":109792,"text":"for their countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111573,"text":"And the West is engaging with that."},{"time":113675,"text":"The West has given debt forgiveness programs"},{"time":115994,"text":"which have halved sub-Saharan debt"},{"time":118497,"text":"from about 70 percent of GDP down to about 40."},{"time":122215,"text":"At the same time, our debt level's gone up to 120"},{"time":124904,"text":"and we're all feeling slightly miserable"},{"time":126992,"text":"as a result."},{"time":128325,"text":"Politics gets weaker when debt is high."},{"time":131440,"text":"When public sector debt is low,"},{"time":133403,"text":"governments don't have to choose"},{"time":134875,"text":"between investing in education and health"},{"time":137357,"text":"and paying interest on that debt you owe."},{"time":139632,"text":"And it's not just the public sector which is looking so good."},{"time":142854,"text":"The private sector as well."},{"time":144711,"text":"Again, in the West, we have private sector debt"},{"time":147872,"text":"of 200 percent of GDP in Spain,"},{"time":150127,"text":"the U.K., and the U.S."},{"time":152418,"text":"That's an awful lot of debt."},{"time":154493,"text":"Africa, many African countries,"},{"time":157084,"text":"are sitting at 10 to 30 percent of GDP."},{"time":160570,"text":"If there's any continent that can do what China has done --"},{"time":164122,"text":"China's at about 130 percent of GDP on that chart --"},{"time":167539,"text":"if anyone can do what China has done"},{"time":169687,"text":"in the last 30 years,"},{"time":171816,"text":"it'll be Africa in the next 30."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174410,"text":"So they've got great government finances, great private sector debt."},{"time":177132,"text":"Does anyone recognize this? In fact, they do."},{"time":179716,"text":"Foreign direct investment"},{"time":181530,"text":"has poured into Africa in the last 15 years."},{"time":185208,"text":"Back in the '70s,"},{"time":187260,"text":"no one touched the continent with a barge pole."},{"time":190257,"text":"And this investment is actually Western-led."},{"time":192528,"text":"We hear a lot about China,"},{"time":194369,"text":"and they do lend a lot of money,"},{"time":196689,"text":"but 60 percent of the FDI in the last couple of years"},{"time":199264,"text":"has come from Europe, America, Australia, Canada."},{"time":202330,"text":"Ten percent's come from India."},{"time":204936,"text":"And they're investing in energy."},{"time":207166,"text":"Africa produces 10 million barrels a day of oil now."},{"time":210416,"text":"It's the same as Saudi Arabia or Russia."},{"time":213720,"text":"And they're investing in telecoms,"},{"time":215791,"text":"shopping malls."},{"time":217796,"text":"And this very encouraging story, I think,"},{"time":221038,"text":"is partly demographic-led."},{"time":222913,"text":"And it's not just about African demographics."},{"time":226250,"text":"I'm showing you the number of 15- to 24-year-olds"},{"time":229225,"text":"in various parts of the world,"},{"time":231507,"text":"and the blue line is the one I want you to focus on for a second."},{"time":234898,"text":"Ten years ago, say you're Foxconn"},{"time":237353,"text":"setting up an iPhone factory, by chance."},{"time":240068,"text":"You might choose China,"},{"time":241688,"text":"which is the bulk of that East Asian blue line,"},{"time":243890,"text":"where there's 200 million young people,"},{"time":245834,"text":"and every year until 2010 that's getting bigger."},{"time":250679,"text":"Which means you're going to have new guys"},{"time":252983,"text":"knocking on the door saying, \"Give us a job,\""},{"time":255345,"text":"and, \"I don't need a big pay rise, just please give me a job.\""},{"time":258580,"text":"Now, that's completely changed now."},{"time":261168,"text":"This decade, we're going to see a 20- to 30-percent"},{"time":264312,"text":"fall in the number of 15- to 24-year-olds in China."},{"time":268423,"text":"So where do you set up your new factory?"},{"time":271624,"text":"You look at South Asia, and people are."},{"time":273411,"text":"They're looking at Pakistan and Bangladesh,"},{"time":275466,"text":"and they're also looking at Africa."},{"time":277857,"text":"And they're looking at Africa"},{"time":279648,"text":"because that yellow line is showing you"},{"time":282162,"text":"that the number of young Africans"},{"time":283822,"text":"is going to continue to get bigger"},{"time":285413,"text":"decade after decade after decade out to 2050."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290832,"text":"Now, there's a problem with lots of young people"},{"time":293696,"text":"coming into any market,"},{"time":295646,"text":"particularly when they're young men."},{"time":297190,"text":"A bit dangerous, sometimes."},{"time":299516,"text":"I think one of the crucial factors"},{"time":301474,"text":"is how educated is that demographic?"},{"time":304895,"text":"If you look at the red line here,"},{"time":306827,"text":"what you're going to see is that in 1975,"},{"time":308503,"text":"just nine percent of kids"},{"time":310592,"text":"were in secondary school education"},{"time":312992,"text":"in sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":315650,"text":"Would you set up a factory"},{"time":317417,"text":"in sub-Sahara in the mid-1970s?"},{"time":319307,"text":"Nobody else did."},{"time":320627,"text":"They chose instead Turkey and Mexico"},{"time":323280,"text":"to set up the textiles factories,"},{"time":325776,"text":"because their education levels"},{"time":327234,"text":"were 25 to 30 percent."},{"time":330135,"text":"Today, sub-Sahara is at the levels"},{"time":333596,"text":"that Turkey and Mexico were at in 1975."},{"time":337332,"text":"They will get the textiles jobs"},{"time":340511,"text":"that will take people out of rural poverty"},{"time":343191,"text":"and put them on the road to industrialization and wealth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347855,"text":"So what's Africa looking like today?"},{"time":350914,"text":"This is how I look at Africa."},{"time":352575,"text":"It's a bit odd, because I'm an economist."},{"time":354399,"text":"Each little box is about a billion dollars,"},{"time":356310,"text":"and you see that I pay an awful lot of attention"},{"time":358027,"text":"to Nigeria sitting there in the middle."},{"time":360319,"text":"South Africa is playing a role."},{"time":362484,"text":"But when I'm thinking about the future,"},{"time":364563,"text":"I'm actually most interested"},{"time":367114,"text":"in Central, Western and Southern Africa."},{"time":369879,"text":"If I look at Africa by population,"},{"time":372441,"text":"East Africa stands out"},{"time":373810,"text":"as so much potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375794,"text":"And I'm showing you something else with these maps."},{"time":378826,"text":"I'm showing you democracy versus autocracy."},{"time":381568,"text":"Fragile democracies is the beige color."},{"time":384821,"text":"Strong democracies are the orange color."},{"time":387464,"text":"And what you'll see here is that most Africans"},{"time":390194,"text":"are now living in democracies."},{"time":394013,"text":"Why does that matter?"},{"time":396189,"text":"Because what people want"},{"time":398623,"text":"is what politicians try,"},{"time":400758,"text":"they don't always succeed, but they try and deliver."},{"time":403849,"text":"And what you've got is a reinforcing positive circle going on."},{"time":406496,"text":"In Ghana in the elections, in December 2012,"},{"time":409372,"text":"the battle between the two candidates"},{"time":411602,"text":"was over education."},{"time":414875,"text":"One guy offered free secondary school education"},{"time":416868,"text":"to all, not just 30 percent."},{"time":419216,"text":"The other guy had to say,"},{"time":420535,"text":"I'm going to build 50 new schools."},{"time":422662,"text":"He won by a margin."},{"time":425521,"text":"So democracy is encouraging governments"},{"time":428571,"text":"to invest in education."},{"time":430171,"text":"Education is helping growth and investment,"},{"time":432256,"text":"and that's giving budget revenues,"},{"time":433668,"text":"which is giving governments more money,"},{"time":435507,"text":"which is helping growth through education."},{"time":438713,"text":"It's a positive, virtuous circle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441248,"text":"But I get asked this question,"},{"time":443809,"text":"and this particular question makes me quite sad:"},{"time":446895,"text":"It's, \"But what about corruption?"},{"time":449426,"text":"How can you invest in Africa when there's corruption?\""},{"time":453530,"text":"And what makes me sad about it"},{"time":455171,"text":"is that this graph here is showing you"},{"time":457196,"text":"that the biggest correlation with corruption is wealth."},{"time":461161,"text":"When you're poor, corruption is not your biggest priority."},{"time":465707,"text":"And the countries on the right hand side,"},{"time":467820,"text":"you'll see the per capita GDP,"},{"time":469543,"text":"basically every country"},{"time":471368,"text":"with a per capita GDP of, say, less than 5,000 dollars,"},{"time":474863,"text":"has got a corruption score"},{"time":477083,"text":"of roughly, what's that, about three?"},{"time":480118,"text":"Three out of 10. That's not good."},{"time":482401,"text":"Every poor country is corrupt."},{"time":484765,"text":"Every rich country is relatively uncorrupt."},{"time":488891,"text":"How do you get from poverty and corruption"},{"time":492894,"text":"to wealth and less corruption?"},{"time":495163,"text":"You see the middle class grow."},{"time":497355,"text":"And the way to do that is to invest,"},{"time":500842,"text":"not to say I'm not investing in that continent"},{"time":504222,"text":"because there's too much corruption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506499,"text":"Now, I don't want to be an apologist for corruption."},{"time":509176,"text":"I've been arrested because I refused to pay a bribe --"},{"time":512115,"text":"not in Africa, actually."},{"time":514227,"text":"But what I'm saying here is that"},{"time":515925,"text":"we can make a difference"},{"time":517715,"text":"and we can do that by investing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520621,"text":"Now I'm going to let you in on a little not-so-secret."},{"time":524128,"text":"Economists aren't great at forecasting."},{"time":526995,"text":"Because the question really is, what happens next?"},{"time":529107,"text":"And if you go back to the year 2000,"},{"time":531631,"text":"what you'll find is The Economist"},{"time":533394,"text":"had a very famous cover, \"The Hopeless Continent,\""},{"time":536562,"text":"and what they'd done is they'd looked at growth"},{"time":538744,"text":"in Africa over the previous 10 years -- two percent --"},{"time":542874,"text":"and they said,"},{"time":544978,"text":"what's going to happen in the next 10 years?"},{"time":547511,"text":"They assumed two percent,"},{"time":549890,"text":"and that made it a pretty hopeless story,"},{"time":551783,"text":"because population growth was two and a half."},{"time":554933,"text":"People got poorer in Africa in the 1990s."},{"time":557713,"text":"Now 2012, The Economist has a new cover,"},{"time":561151,"text":"and what does that new cover show?"},{"time":562997,"text":"That new cover shows, well, Africa rising,"},{"time":565980,"text":"because the growth over the last 10 years"},{"time":567707,"text":"has been about five and a half percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570327,"text":"I would like to see if you can all now become economists,"},{"time":573853,"text":"because if growth for the last 10 years"},{"time":576368,"text":"has been five and a half percent,"},{"time":578488,"text":"what do you think the IMF is forecasting"},{"time":580191,"text":"for the next five years of growth in Africa?"},{"time":583211,"text":"Very good. I think you're secretly saying"},{"time":585986,"text":"to your head, probably five and a half percent."},{"time":588168,"text":"You're all economists, and I think,"},{"time":590110,"text":"like most economists, wrong."},{"time":592592,"text":"No offense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594688,"text":"What I like to do is try and find the countries"},{"time":597569,"text":"that are doing exactly what Africa has already done,"},{"time":601730,"text":"and it means that jump from 1,800 years of nothing"},{"time":605128,"text":"to whoof, suddenly shooting through the roof."},{"time":608175,"text":"India is one of those examples."},{"time":610829,"text":"This is Indian growth from 1960 to 2010."},{"time":614948,"text":"Ignore the scale on the bottom for a second."},{"time":617862,"text":"Actually, for the first 20 years,"},{"time":620232,"text":"the '60s and '70s, India didn't really grow."},{"time":623275,"text":"It grew at two percent"},{"time":625336,"text":"when population growth was about two and a half."},{"time":628416,"text":"If that's familiar, that's exactly what happened"},{"time":630596,"text":"in sub-Sahara in the '80s and the '90s."},{"time":632891,"text":"And then something happened in 1980."},{"time":634665,"text":"Boom! India began to explode."},{"time":636888,"text":"It wasn't a \"Hindu rate of growth,\""},{"time":639172,"text":"\"democracies can't grow.\" Actually India could."},{"time":642228,"text":"And if I lay sub-Saharan growth"},{"time":645034,"text":"on top of the Indian growth story,"},{"time":647302,"text":"it's remarkably similar."},{"time":649918,"text":"Twenty years of not much growth"},{"time":652205,"text":"and a trend line which is actually telling you"},{"time":653759,"text":"that sub-Saharan African growth is"},{"time":655749,"text":"slightly better than India."},{"time":658310,"text":"And if I then lay developing Asia on top of this,"},{"time":661745,"text":"I'm saying India is 20 years ahead of Africa,"},{"time":664569,"text":"I'm saying developing Asia is 10 years ahead of India,"},{"time":668675,"text":"I can draw out some forecasts"},{"time":670852,"text":"for the next 30 to 40 years"},{"time":673172,"text":"which I think are better"},{"time":675242,"text":"than the ones where you're looking backwards."},{"time":678094,"text":"And that tells me this:"},{"time":680441,"text":"that Africa is going to go"},{"time":682223,"text":"from a $2 trillion economy today"},{"time":685260,"text":"to a $29 trillion economy by 2050."},{"time":689532,"text":"Now that's bigger than Europe and America"},{"time":691540,"text":"put together in today's money."},{"time":694998,"text":"Life expectancy is going to go up by 13 years."},{"time":698918,"text":"The population's going to double"},{"time":700656,"text":"from one billion to two billion,"},{"time":702109,"text":"so household incomes are going to go up sevenfold"},{"time":705459,"text":"in the next 35 years."},{"time":708323,"text":"And when I present this in Africa --"},{"time":711440,"text":"Nairobi, Lagos, Accra -- I get one question."},{"time":715244,"text":"\"Charlie, why are you so pessimistic?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":720112,"text":"And you know what?"},{"time":721955,"text":"Actually, I think they've got a point."},{"time":724344,"text":"Am I really saying that there can be nothing learned,"},{"time":726816,"text":"yes from the positives in Asia and India,"},{"time":730100,"text":"but also the negatives?"},{"time":731478,"text":"Perhaps Africa can avoid some of the mistakes that have been made."},{"time":734040,"text":"Surely, the technologies that we're talking about here"},{"time":737435,"text":"this last week,"},{"time":739044,"text":"surely some of these can perhaps"},{"time":740988,"text":"help Africa grow even faster?"},{"time":743716,"text":"And I think here we can play a role."},{"time":746151,"text":"Because technology does let you help."},{"time":748994,"text":"You can go and download"},{"time":751133,"text":"some of the great African literature"},{"time":753168,"text":"from the Internet now."},{"time":754967,"text":"No, not right now, just 30 seconds."},{"time":757440,"text":"You can go and buy some of the great tunes."},{"time":759630,"text":"My iPod's full of them."},{"time":761361,"text":"Buy African products."},{"time":763051,"text":"Go on holiday and see for yourself"},{"time":765016,"text":"the change that's happening."},{"time":766565,"text":"Invest."},{"time":767970,"text":"Perhaps hire people, give them the skills"},{"time":770096,"text":"that they can take back to Africa,"},{"time":772365,"text":"and their companies will grow an awful lot faster"},{"time":774630,"text":"than most of ours here in the West."},{"time":777280,"text":"And then you and I can help make sure"},{"time":781581,"text":"that for Africa, the 21st century is their century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785710,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787520,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}